for wrongful death here.

310
00:12:19.260 --> 00:12:22.219
One moment. please. Your Honor.

311
00:12:23.612 --> 00:12:25.440
Just a hunch. but I don't
think she's buying it.

312
00:12:25.483 --> 00:12:26.615
Well. she's a new judge.

313
00:12:26.658 --> 00:12:27.877
She's just trying
to make her mark.

314
00:12:27.921 --> 00:12:29.226
You got a Plan B?

315
00:12:29.270 --> 00:12:30.837
I could argue
a civil rights violation.

316
00:12:30.880 --> 00:12:32.664
but that's more of a stretch
than wrongful death.

317
00:12:32.708 --> 00:12:33.927
I doubt she'll go
for that either.

318
00:12:33.970 --> 00:12:36.320
Well. we need something
she will go for.

319
00:12:36.364 --> 00:12:37.844
Well. do you have
any suggestions?

320
00:12:37.887 --> 00:12:39.715
'Cause in about ten seconds.
she's about to toss our case.

321
00:12:39.759 --> 00:12:40.934
and then we're nowhere.

322
00:12:40.977 --> 00:12:41.630
Okay. well. I'll come
up with something.

323
00:12:41.673 --> 00:12:43.414
just keep her talking.

324
00:12:45.155 --> 00:12:47.375
Your Honor.
if it please the court.

325
00:12:47.418 --> 00:12:50.160
we would like to amend
our existing complaint.

326
00:12:50.204 --> 00:12:52.249
Taylor. can you boot up
your hard drive.

327
00:12:52.293 --> 00:12:54.338
or whatever it is
you do with that thing.

328
00:12:54.382 --> 00:12:56.384
Now isn't a great time. Oh.

329
00:12:56.427 --> 00:12:58.386
I'm sorry.
I will try and arrange

330
00:12:58.429 --> 00:13:00.301
my emergencies better
in the future.

331
00:13:00.344 --> 00:13:03.565
I'd love to help. I can't.
We're completely off-line and...

332
00:13:04.871 --> 00:13:06.437
Oh. wait. We're back.

333
00:13:06.481 --> 00:13:07.874
We're on line.

334
00:13:07.917 --> 00:13:09.701
Great. Listen. I need you
to do something for me.

335
00:13:09.745 --> 00:13:12.313
Yes. in about ten minutes
when my system reboots.

336
00:13:12.356 --> 00:13:15.359
I don't have time.

337
00:13:15.403 --> 00:13:16.839
You know what? Never mind.

338
00:13:16.883 --> 00:13:19.537
Viridipoint
is a corporate entity.

339
00:13:19.581 --> 00:13:21.626
How does your
civil rights claim apply?

340
00:13:21.670 --> 00:13:23.890
Law enforcement is
a state function. Your Honor.

341
00:13:23.933 --> 00:13:26.849
By providing investigative leads
to the NYPD.

342
00:13:26.893 --> 00:13:29.547
Viridipoint is. in effect.
a state actor.

343
00:13:31.027 --> 00:13:32.550
I don't see it.

344
00:13:32.594 --> 00:13:34.161
Nice try. but I'm afraid
we're gonna...

345
00:13:35.684 --> 00:13:37.729
All right. everyone.
take it easy.

346
00:13:37.773 --> 00:13:39.035
We'll have
a brief recess

347
00:13:39.079 --> 00:13:41.124
while we get this sorted out.

348
00:13:44.911 --> 00:13:46.608
Everyone out
this way. please.

349
00:13:47.696 --> 00:13:50.177
Did you...?I plead the Fifth.
Let's go.

350
00:13:55.356 --> 00:13:57.358
We got five minutes
to come up with an argument

351
00:13:57.401 --> 00:13:59.839
that Judge Preston
won't kick.

352
00:13:59.882 --> 00:14:01.057
The judge called

353
00:14:01.101 --> 00:14:03.103
V-Point's facial recognition
program a tool.

354
00:14:03.146 --> 00:14:05.975
Yeah. "A tool is only as good
as the user" argument. yeah.Right.

355
00:14:06.019 --> 00:14:08.978
So Corey Rice died
because V-Point's tool.

356
00:14:09.022 --> 00:14:11.328
its... product.

357
00:14:11.372 --> 00:14:13.113
didn't work as advertised.

358
00:14:13.156 --> 00:14:16.029
and that's not on the user.
That's false advertising.

359
00:14:16.072 --> 00:14:19.032
Wait a minute. you want to sue
for deceptive trade practice?

360
00:14:19.075 --> 00:14:21.599
Well. Don Quixote. you wanted
to tilt at windmills. Try it.

361
00:14:21.643 --> 00:14:23.732
I got to go.You're not sticking around
for this?

362
00:14:23.775 --> 00:14:25.690
Well. some schmuck
pulled the fire alarm.

363
00:14:25.734 --> 00:14:28.215
I can't stick around for that.

364
00:14:28.258 --> 00:14:30.086
Viridipoint misrepresented

365
00:14:30.130 --> 00:14:32.784
material facts to their
customers to perpetrate a fraud.

366
00:14:32.828 --> 00:14:34.308
and in so doing engaged

367
00:14:34.351 --> 00:14:36.049
in a pattern of deceptive
trade practices. Your Honor.

368
00:14:36.092 --> 00:14:39.052
Vernice Rice wasn't a customer
of Viridipoint. Your Honor.

369
00:14:39.095 --> 00:14:42.403
In that case. I don't see
how she has standing.

370
00:14:42.446 --> 00:14:44.884
Remington v. Soto.
Your Honor.

371
00:14:44.927 --> 00:14:48.017
