I guess he was right.

783
00:32:26.945 --> 00:32:28.555
What happens now?

784
00:32:28.598 --> 00:32:30.949
Convince our client to accept
a settlement she doesn't want

785
00:32:30.992 --> 00:32:32.341
or lose in court.

786
00:32:34.517 --> 00:32:35.997
V-Point's offer
is substantial.

787
00:32:36.041 --> 00:32:38.043
And they've agreed
to suspend licensing

788
00:32:38.086 --> 00:32:40.088
the facial recognition
software to

789
00:32:40.132 --> 00:32:42.308
New York state law enforcement.

790
00:32:42.351 --> 00:32:45.224
The police couldn't
use it anymore?

791
00:32:45.267 --> 00:32:48.009
In New York state.

792
00:32:48.053 --> 00:32:50.142
Elsewhere. they can.

793
00:32:51.795 --> 00:32:54.885
Where's the other shoe?
What do they want?

794
00:32:54.929 --> 00:32:58.193
There's a non-disparagement
clause. which means that

795
00:32:58.237 --> 00:33:01.196
you would have to refrain from
making any public statements

796
00:33:01.240 --> 00:33:04.243
that were critical
of V-Point or its technology.

797
00:33:04.286 --> 00:33:05.635
forever.

798
00:33:05.679 --> 00:33:08.160
They want me to go away.

799
00:33:09.552 --> 00:33:11.554
Forget Corey ever existed.

800
00:33:11.598 --> 00:33:14.688
They are buying
your silence. yes.

801
00:33:15.776 --> 00:33:17.996
That money they're offering...

802
00:33:19.606 --> 00:33:23.479
I know charities that could
put it to good use.

803
00:33:23.523 --> 00:33:27.788
And for the NYPD to give up
facial recognition...

804
00:33:29.398 --> 00:33:30.617
That's something.

805
00:33:30.660 --> 00:33:32.053
It is. and

806
00:33:32.097 --> 00:33:34.186
if we go in front of a jury.

807
00:33:34.229 --> 00:33:36.362
I promise you.

808
00:33:36.405 --> 00:33:39.843
you'll get nothing.
absolutely nothing.

809
00:33:46.676 --> 00:33:48.287
Would you sign it?

810
00:33:48.330 --> 00:33:51.594
If it meant I had to be silent
about the death of my child.

811
00:33:51.638 --> 00:33:54.771
I would politely tell them
how to fold that offer.

812
00:33:54.815 --> 00:33:57.687
and I would tell them
exactly where to put it.

813
00:34:01.996 --> 00:34:05.565
I wasn't raised to be a quitter.

814
00:34:05.608 --> 00:34:07.828
No sense starting now.

815
00:34:10.700 --> 00:34:12.963
Corey always called me

816
00:34:13.007 --> 00:34:15.618
as soon as he
got to work.

817
00:34:15.662 --> 00:34:18.708
He worked a lot of nights.

818
00:34:18.752 --> 00:34:20.841
Didn't matter how late.

819
00:34:20.884 --> 00:34:23.278
he always made sure
to let me know

820
00:34:23.322 --> 00:34:25.628
he was all right...

821
00:34:25.672 --> 00:34:27.413
but not that night.

822
00:34:27.456 --> 00:34:29.110
Mrs. Rice.

823
00:34:29.154 --> 00:34:30.981
when you found out
that Corey was dead.

824
00:34:31.025 --> 00:34:33.680
did the authorities tell you
what had happened?

825
00:34:33.723 --> 00:34:36.639
I was told my son

826
00:34:36.683 --> 00:34:38.467
had been misidentified

827
00:34:38.511 --> 00:34:41.122
by an algorithm.

828
00:34:41.166 --> 00:34:43.820
An algorithm.

829
00:34:43.864 --> 00:34:46.954
How can you protect
against an algorithm?

830
00:34:48.434 --> 00:34:50.479
I taught my son

831
00:34:50.523 --> 00:34:53.178
keep your hands in the open.

832
00:34:53.221 --> 00:34:55.397
walk. don't run.

833
00:34:55.441 --> 00:34:57.182
"Yes. Officer.

834
00:34:57.225 --> 00:34:59.053
No. Officer."

835
00:35:00.315 --> 00:35:03.666
That's what we need
to teach our children

836
00:35:03.710 --> 00:35:07.148
so they can get through
this world.

837
00:35:07.192 --> 00:35:09.063
To survive.

838
00:35:11.718 --> 00:35:14.721
He did everything
he was supposed to.

839
00:35:14.764 --> 00:35:17.245
but they still put
a target on his back

840
00:35:17.289 --> 00:35:20.292
because some machine
said it was all right.

841
00:35:21.684 --> 00:35:23.947
Mrs. Rice. you don't believe

842
00:35:23.991 --> 00:35:26.036
Viridipoint's claim of being

843
00:35:26.080 --> 00:35:29.344
99.7% accurate. do you?

844
00:35:30.911 --> 00:35:32.956
Not for my son.

845
00:35:33.000 --> 00:35:36.264
Not for anyone whose
skin looked like his.

846
00:35:37.483 --> 00:35:40.312
He was a fine
young man.

847
00:35:40.355 --> 00:35:43.358
and he would've had so
much to give this world

848
00:35:43.402 --> 00:35:45.055
if someone at Viridipoint hadn't

849
00:35:45.099 --> 00:35:48.276
thrown up their hands
and said. "Close enough."

850
00:35:48.320 --> 00:35:50.322
No.

851
00:35:50.365 --> 00:35:52.193
I can't accept that.

852
00:35:52.237 --> 00:35:54.282
Not if "close enough"

853
00:35:54.326 --> 00:35:57.764
means someone else might
have to bury their child.

854
00:36:01.724 --> 00:36:03.422
No.

855
00:36:04.466 --> 00:36:07.252
I have nothing further.
Your Honor.

856
00:36:14.955 --> 00:36:17.610
Ladies and gentlemen
of the jury.

857
00:36:17.653 --> 00:36:19.177
have you reached a verdict?

858
00:36:19.220 --> 00:36:22.310
We have. Your Honor.

859
00:36:24.007 --> 00:36:26.488
We the jury find the defendant.

860
00:36:26.532 --> 00:36:29.839
Viridipoint AI.

861
00:36:29.883 --> 00:36:33.321
not liable under
the consumer protection laws

862
00:36:33.365 --> 00:36:34.540
of the State of New York.

863
00:36:34.583 --> 00:36:36.237
The court thanks the members

864
00:36:36.281 --> 00:36:37.804
of the jury
for their service.

865
00:36:37.847 --> 00:36:40.154
Court is adjourned.

866
00:36:48.728 --> 00:36:51.470
Mrs. Rice. I'm not sure
I deserve that.

867
00:36:53.472 --> 00:36:56.170
You let my son speak.

868
00:36:56.214 --> 00:36:59.129
Everyone in this courtroom
knows who he was

869
00:36:59.173 --> 00:37:02.437
and what was taken from him.

870
00:37:02.481 --> 00:37:04.222
You gave me that much.

871
00:37:04.265 --> 00:37:06.311
We still lost.

872
00:37:06.354 --> 00:37:09.270
and I don't know why
I'm not surprised.

873
00:37:09.314 --> 00:37:10.924
Corey used to say.

874
00:37:10.967 --> 00:37:12.404
"Fight for keeps.

875
00:37:12.447 --> 00:37:15.276
so you can keep fighting."

876
00:37:15.320 --> 00:37:17.670
So. keep fighting.

877
00:37:20.020 --> 00:37:21.500
Keep fighting.

878
00:37:25.939 --> 00:37:27.462
Goodbye. Dr. Bull.

879
00:37:27.506 --> 00:37:30.378
It's been an honor.
Mrs. Rice.

880
00:37:37.167 --> 00:37:39.300
I keep thinking about
V-point's settlement offer.

881
00:37:39.344 --> 00:37:40.910
What about it?

882
00:37:40.954 --> 00:37:43.043
Well. people try to settle
'cause they're scared of losing.

883
00:37:43.086 --> 00:37:44.697
Yeah. usually.

884
00:37:44.740 --> 00:37:47.308
When they made the offer.
they were winning. no question.

885
00:37:47.352 --> 00:37:48.831
so what are they
scared of?

886
00:37:54.359 --> 00:37:56.404
The financial documents
that Taylor dug up

887
00:37:56.448 --> 00:38:00.147
contain two sets of books.
One public. one private.

888
00:38:00.190 --> 00:38:02.367
V-Point's a publicly
held company.

889
00:38:02.410 --> 00:38:04.717
If they've been feeding
investors fake numbers.

890
00:38:04.760 --> 00:38:06.284
that is securities fraud.

891
00:38:06.327 --> 00:38:07.850
Yup.

892
00:38:07.894 --> 00:38:09.591
Securities fraud?
What did I miss?

893
00:38:09.635 --> 00:38:12.899
I think we just figured out why
V-Point was so keen to settle.

894
00:38:12.942 --> 00:38:14.422
Their offer came right after

895
00:38:14.466 --> 00:38:16.511
Taylor hacked into Voight's
super-secret computer.

896
00:38:16.555 --> 00:38:19.645
which made us wonder if he knew
he'd been hacked and was scared

897
00:38:19.688 --> 00:38:20.820
about what
we might find.

898
00:38:20.863 --> 00:38:22.648
So. Voight offered
to settle.

899
00:38:22.691 --> 00:38:25.955
so we would stop digging
and not find his cooked books.

900
00:38:25.999 --> 00:38:27.914
He must've crapped his pants
when we turned him down.

901
00:38:27.957 --> 00:38:29.655
He thought we were
gonna bust him.

902
00:38:29.698 --> 00:38:32.701
Well. is there anyone
stopping us from doing that now?

903
00:38:32.745 --> 00:38:34.573
Well. the way Taylor
got these was not what

904
00:38:34.616 --> 00:38:36.096
you'd call kosher.

905
00:38:36.139 --> 00:38:38.751
We release them. we put her
in legal jeopardy.

906
00:38:39.839 --> 00:38:42.363
Right. but there's got to be
a way around that.

907
00:38:42.407 --> 00:38:46.454
Hey. doesn't the SEC
have an anonymous tip line?

908
00:38:47.890 --> 00:38:49.414
Why. yes.

909
00:38:49.457 --> 00:38:50.937
Yes. it does.

910
00:38:50.980 --> 00:38:53.243
Mr. Voight!
Mr. Voight! Mr. Voight!

911
00:38:53.287 --> 00:38:55.550
What do you have to say
about the accusations?

912
00:38:55.594 --> 00:38:57.900
They just said Voight
is facing 20 years

913
00:38:57.944 --> 00:38:59.641
and up to $12 million
in fines.

914
00:38:59.685 --> 00:39:02.383
Yeah. and the company's
filing for bankruptcy.

915
00:39:02.427 --> 00:39:04.646
So long. Viridipoint.

916
00:39:05.995 --> 00:39:09.521
This just came
for you. Wine club?

917
00:39:09.564 --> 00:39:11.610
Not unless you signed me up.

918
00:39:21.881 --> 00:39:23.404
Who's that from?

919
00:39:23.448 --> 00:39:25.972
Me.

920
00:39:26.015 --> 00:39:27.800
a long time ago.

921
00:39:27.843 --> 00:39:30.063
I'm going to get some food.
Want to come?

922
00:39:30.106 --> 00:39:31.630
Uh. thanks. but...

923
00:39:31.673 --> 00:39:33.545
I need to make a call.

924
00:39:36.809 --> 00:39:37.810
Marissa!

925
00:39:37.853 --> 00:39:39.289
Oh...

926
00:39:39.333 --> 00:39:41.857
Why do I feel like a man
who's about to be let down easy?

927
00:39:41.901 --> 00:39:45.513
Bradley. your offer
was incredibly generous.

928
00:39:45.557 --> 00:39:47.472
but...

929
00:39:47.515 --> 00:39:49.299
I'm afraid my answer is no.

930
00:39:49.343 --> 00:39:52.694
Well... you'd be a tremendous
asset to any company

931
00:39:52.738 --> 00:39:55.958
for all the reasons
I've stated repeatedly.

932
00:39:56.002 --> 00:39:58.613
but the thing I like
about you most of all

933
00:39:58.657 --> 00:40:00.876
is your sense of loyalty.

934
00:40:00.920 --> 00:40:02.356
Thank you.

935
00:40:02.400 --> 00:40:04.010
Look. I know we went over

936
00:40:04.053 --> 00:40:06.142
the compensation package
earlier. but...

937
00:40:06.186 --> 00:40:09.581
there was one perk
I didn't mention.

938
00:40:09.624 --> 00:40:11.147
Can I show it to you?

939
00:40:11.191 --> 00:40:12.714
Sure.

940
00:40:17.589 --> 00:40:19.417
What do you think?

941
00:40:32.560 --> 00:40:34.562
You got a minute?

942
00:40:34.606 --> 00:40:36.912
Hey. You bet I do.

943
00:40:36.956 --> 00:40:38.566
In fact...

944
00:40:38.610 --> 00:40:39.915
I'm glad you came by.

945
00:40:39.959 --> 00:40:42.265
because I got
a little something

946
00:40:42.309 --> 00:40:44.877
I wanted us to share once
you signed your deal memo.

947
00:40:44.920 --> 00:40:47.227
but. what the heck.
let's crack her open now.

948
00:40:48.576 --> 00:40:49.925
2010 Barolo.

949
00:40:49.969 --> 00:40:51.884
Don't ask how much
it cost. 'cause...

950
00:40:51.927 --> 00:40:53.233
it would make me blush.

951
00:40:53.276 --> 00:40:55.061
You didn't have to do that.

952
00:40:55.104 --> 00:40:58.586
Yes. I did. and
that is precisely

953
00:40:58.630 --> 00:40:59.935
the point.

954
00:41:01.546 --> 00:41:03.939
Isn't that the best sound
in the world?

955
00:41:05.941 --> 00:41:09.467
I have to tell you something.

956
00:41:13.514 --> 00:41:16.125
You're leaving...

957
00:41:16.169 --> 00:41:17.692
to work with Lena.

958
00:41:19.389 --> 00:41:21.043
I'm sorry.

959
00:41:23.306 --> 00:41:25.134
But...

960
00:41:25.178 --> 00:41:26.962
Okay.

961
00:41:27.006 --> 00:41:29.661
We... did talk.

962
00:41:29.704 --> 00:41:31.358
and I was giving you everything

963
00:41:31.401 --> 00:41:33.926
that you wanted.You are.

964
00:41:33.969 --> 00:41:36.581
But...

965
00:41:36.624 --> 00:41:39.235
What is he giving you?

966
00:41:44.327 --> 00:41:46.591
You... Okay.

967
00:41:46.634 --> 00:41:48.680
You want your name
above the door?

968
00:41:48.723 --> 00:41:50.551
You never asked for that.

969
00:41:50.595 --> 00:41:52.466
Mm. you're right. I didn't.

970
00:41:52.510 --> 00:41:53.946
With him. I didn't have to.

971
00:41:53.989 --> 00:41:56.862
Okay. well. technically.
my name's not above the door

972
00:41:56.905 --> 00:41:59.038
'cause it's just TAC.
but if you would like to change

973
00:41:59.081 --> 00:42:00.430
the name of the company...I want to be somewhere

974
00:42:00.474 --> 00:42:02.128
my value is known.You are...

975
00:42:02.171 --> 00:42:05.653
Not something that I have
to argue for or negotiate.

976
00:42:09.744 --> 00:42:12.355
I'm gonna go get my things.

977
00:42:12.399 --> 00:42:14.444
I'll be out in an hour.

978
00:42:17.752 --> 00:42:18.536
Goodbye.
